Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the interior is covered with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and remains of four lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Frankfort 1933 / The Cenotaph of Seti I at Abydos (no.7 (p.95,pl.xciii))
Jasnow & Pouls Wegner 2006-2007 / Demotic Ostraca from North Abydos (p.51)
Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393859) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393859)
